article.headline: Stetson 74, St. Leo 69
article.story: DELAND, Fla. -- Liam McInerney scored 13 points and Aaron Graham made all eight of his free throws to help Stetson hold off St. Leo 74-69 on Saturday. Division II St. Leo (2-2) kept it close the majority of the game, trailing 46-41 after a Dominick Robinson 3-pointer. But McInerney scored eight points in three minutes to give Stetson (3-1) a 55-47 lead with 9:22 left to play. Robinson came up big again, knocking down a layup and the subsequent foul shot to tie the game 67-67. McInerney then converted a 3-point play of his own, tipping in a Chris Perez miss and nailing his free throw to extend the Hatters' lead to 70-67 with 49 seconds remaining in the game. A Trent Thomas layup narrowed the lead to one, 70-69, with 31 seconds to play, but Aaron Graham hit four straight free throws to put the game out of reach.
